h-foreground regions. We also find\nthat it should be possible to detect the radial BAO signature with high\nsignificance in the full redshift range. We conclude that a 21cm experiment\ncarried out by the SKA should be able to make direct measurements of the\nexpansion rate $H(z)$ with competitive per-cent level precision on redshifts\n$z\\lesssim2.5$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 31 Aug 2016 20:01:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-01-25"}
